  "prompt": "Can I take Nyquil and Benadryl at the same time?",
  "response": "It's generally not recommended to take Nyquil and Benadryl at the same time because both contain antihistamines, which can lead to excessive drowsiness and other potential side effects. Nyquil already contains doxylamine, an antihistamine that causes drowsiness, similar to diphenhydramine, the active ingredient in Benadryl.\n\nTaking both medications together can increase the risk of side effects such as:\n\n- Severe drowsiness\n- Dizziness\n- Dry mouth\n- Blurred vision\n- Constipation\n- Difficulty urinating\n\nIf you need relief from symptoms that both medications address, it's best to consult with a healthcare professional before combining them. They can provide guidance based on your specific health needs and conditions.",
